</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Carl Everett, Troy O'Leary, Jason Varitek and Morgan
Burkhart tied a Red Sox record by homering in a nine-run fourth inning and
Boston beat the Minnesota Twins 11-8 Monday night. The Red Sox matched a club
mark for homers in an inning last accomplished July 18, 1998, against Detroit.
Boston has done it eight times since 1940.
</P>
