All-Star break, one more than Ken Griffey Jr. had in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   After falling behind 6-1 in the third, the Angels closed to 7-6
with one run in the fourth, on Anderson's second homer of the game
and 23rd of the season, and a four-run sixth, keyed by Benjie
Molina's two-run shot.
</P>
