<P>
   Kazuhiro Sasaki pitched the ninth for his 17th save.
</P>
<P>
   Olerud had a sacrifice fly as Seattle went up 2-0 in the first,
then doubled with the bases loaded to drive in three more runs for
a 5-0 lead in the second.
</P>
<P>
   Although they are only 3-3 in their last six games, the Mariners
have won 18 of their last 23 and, at 48-32, have the best record
through 80 games in their club history.
</P>
<P>
   Ken Hill (4-5) had trouble getting the ball over the plate and
was rocked for five runs on four hits and five walks in just 1 2-3
innings.
Notes: The Mariners' best mark through 80 games prior to this year
was 47-33 in 1997. ... The Angels' Darin Erstad, a late scratch
from the starting lineup because of tightness in his lower back,
had a pinch-hit single in the eighth. Erstad, who has missed only
one game this season, has a major league-leading 131 hits. ...
Anderson is 16-for-34 lifetime against Moyer, including three
homers. Anderson's other two-homer game was May 25 of last year
against Baltimore. He's the seventh different Angel to homer twice
in a game this year. ... Glaus' double in the sixth snapped a
0-for-20 slump in which he struck out 13 times. ... Molina's nine
homers match the highest number by an Angels catcher in an entire
season since Lance Parrish had 19 in 1991. Jim Leyritz and Todd
Greene each homered nine times in 1997.
</P>
