<HEADLINE> One man killed and another injured after being struck by train  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HIGHLAND, N.Y. (AP) - One man was killed and another was
seriously injured after being struck by a freight train in Ulster
County, according to police.
</P>
<P>
   Nakia Barreto, 20, was killed in the accident, according to Town
of Lloyd police. Dennis Hartung, 19, remained in critical condition
at St. Francis Hospital in Poughkeepsie Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   The two men were standing near the train tracks when they were
struck by a northbound CSX train, which was reportedly traveling
between 40 and 45 mph, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Barreto was reportedly struck by the train and thrown onto the
road. He sustained head and body trauma, according to police, who
said Barreto died later at the hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Hartung may have sustained injury to his spleen and underwent
surgery late Monday, according to police. It remained unclear
Monday why the men were standing near the tracks, according to
police who said only CSX employees should have been in the area.
</P>
