<HEADLINE> Conserve Wins Firecracker Cup  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Conserve, ridden by Shane Sellers, set
the early pace and held off Riviera by a neck-length for a
wire-to-wire victory in Tuesday's $287,000 Grade II Firecracker
Breeders' Cup for 3-year-olds and up at Churchill Downs.
</P>
<P>
   Conserve, winner of the Makers Mark Mile at Keeneland in his
last start in April, covered the mile on firm turf in 1:35.12 and
paid $7.60, $3.60 and $2.60.
</P>
<P>
   Riviera, trained by California-based Bobby Frankel and ridden by
Craig Perret, stalked the pace in third but was unable to gain the
lead in the final strides and paid $3.20 and $2.80. King Slayer
finished another two lengths back in third and paid $2.80.
</P>
<P>
   Conserve, the 4-year-old gelded son of Boundary, is owned and
bred by Claiborne Farm and trained by Frank Brothers, who teamed up
to win the Louisville Handicap earlier in the meet with Buff.
Conserve earned $177,940 to increase his lifetime bankroll to
$473,974. The win was his sixth in in 18 career starts.
</P>
</TEXT>
