<HEADLINE> Red Sox Sign Gilkey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Bernard Gilkey got off to a great start in
the American League.
</P>
<P>
   Signed earlier in the day by the Boston Red Sox after 10 seasons
in the NL, Gilkey singled, doubled and then homered in his first
three at-bats Tuesday night against Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   Gilkey, 33, played in 38 games with the Arizona Diamondbacks
this season and became a free agent when he was designated for
assignment June 24. He was hitting .110 and in a 2-for-48 slump
when he was let go.
</P>
<P>
   Gilkey has led NL outfielders in assists three times (1993,
1998, 1997). He had been working out with the Red Sox for several
days before he was signed to a contract.
</P>
<P>
   To make room for Gilkey, Boston designated outfielder Curtis
Pride for assignment.
</P>
<P>
   The Red Sox also recalled left-handed pitcher Tim Young from
Triple-A Pawtucket and optioned infielder Wilton Veras to
Pawtucket.
</P>
</TEXT>
