<HEADLINE> Other Jones Called Up  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Left-hander Bobby M. Jones was recalled Tuesday by
the New York Mets from Norfolk of the International League and was
the loser in a 9-8 defeat to the Florida Marlins.
</P>
<P>
   Jones allowed seven runs -- six earned -- and six hits in four
innings. He walked three and struck out one.
</P>
<P>
   At Norfolk, Jones was 7-3 with a 4.11 ERA with 36 walks and 52
strikeouts in 76 2-3 innings. He made 12 starts and one relief
appearance.
</P>
<P>
   Jones had been with the Mets from June 13-23, and made just one
relief appearance. He allowed no runs, no hits, walked two and
struck out two in one inning at Milwaukee June 16.
</P>
<P>
   Right-hander Jim Mann was optioned to Triple-A Norfolk. He had
no decisions in two appearances with New York. He gave up six hits
and three runs in 2 2-3 innings.
</P>
