<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquakes Jolt Japanese Islands  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- A strong earthquake shook a string of volcanic
islands off Tokyo on Wednesday amid more aftershocks from a
powerful temblor that killed a man last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   There were no immediate reports of damage or injuries from the
quake, which had a preliminary magnitude of 5.0 and struck at 6:51
a.m., said a night duty official at the municipal office on
Miyakejima, an island where about 4,000 people live.
</P>
<P>
   The Meteorological Agency said the latest quake was centered in
''shallow waters'' near the island, 120 miles, south of Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   On Saturday, a magnitude 6.4 earthquake rocked Miyakejima and
nearby Kozushima, where a 34-year-old fisherman was killed by
falling rocks.
</P>
<P>
   Since Saturday, more than 6,000 tremors, about 10 percent of
them strong enough to be felt by people, had been registered on
both islands through Wednesday morning, the Meteorological Agency
said.
</P>
<P>
   About half of the residents on Miyakejima, just southeast of
Kozushima, were allowed to return to their homes last Friday after
fears of a volcanic eruption subsided.
</P>
<P>
   Japan is one of the world's most earthquake-prone nations as it
sits atop four tectonic plates, slabs of land that move across the
earth's surface.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-07-04-00 2203 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000704.0140 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 22:03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moondancer Wins American Handicap  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Dark Moondancer pressed the pace
inside, eventually took the lead in the stretch and went on to win
the $150,000 American Handicap at Hollywood Park on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   A slight favorite at odds of 9-5, the 5-year-old British-bred
justified his support by beating Sardauker by 1&AMP;frac12; lengths. Ridden by
Chris McCarron and carrying high weight of 122 pounds, Dark
Moondancer covered 1[ miles in 1:46 3-5.
</P>
<P>
   McCarron angled his horse off the rail as they neared the far
turn and assumed the lead as the field turned into the stretch. He
slowly drew clear without being seriously threatened.
</P>
<P>
   Sunshine Street, who engaged Dark Moondancer for the early lead,
held on to third -- a neck behind the rallying runner-up.
</P>
<P>
   Dark Moondancer paid $5.80, $3.40 and $2.40. Sardauker, who
carried 113 pounds, paid $5 and $2.80, while Sunshine, carrying 119
pounds, paid $2.60 to show.
</P>
<P>
   The victory was worth $90,000 for owner Charles Cella and
increased Dark Moondancer's career earnings to $775,245.
</P>
<P>
   Falcon Flight, Martiniquais and Takarian rounded out the order
of finish.
</P>
