2-year-old filly champion, bested a field of older fillies and
mares to win the $75,000 Regret Stakes. She was challenged until
the eighth pole, when she drew off to win by five lengths,
finishing the six furlongs in 1:09.2.
</P>
<P>
   Chilukki, the odds-on favorite ridden by Nakatani and carrying
116 pounds, paid $2.40. Superduper Miss was five lengths back in
second in the field of six.
</P>
