the left post in the 26th minute. He also setup Quill's first goal
in the 37th minute during a 2-on-1 break.
</P>
<P>
   D.C. United, the defending league champions, have an MLS-worst
4-12-5 record and have allowed 42 goals. It was just the fifth time
in 17 meetings United lost to Tampa Bay.
</P>
<P>
   The game was stopped 34 minutes into the first half because of
lightning associated with a heavy thunderstorm. Some of the
fireworks for a postgame display went off after a nearby lightning
strike.
</P>
<P>
   The contest was resumed after an 86-minute delay.
</P>
