<HEADLINE> Mariners' Henderson Gets Ejected  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Seattle Mariners left fielder Rickey
Henderson was ejected by plate umpire Bill Welke after looking at a
third strike in the third inning of Tuesday night's game against
the Anaheim Angels.
</P>
<P>
   Henderson, who was called out on a 2-2 pitch in the first
inning, didn't offer at Kent Bottenfield's 0-2 pitch on the inside
corner his next time up.
</P>
<P>
   Henderson never said a word after Welke's arm went up. Close-up
television replays confirmed that Henderson's lips did not move
from the time the pitch came until the time Welke tossed him.
</P>
<P>
   But Welke apparently did not appreciate the fact that Henderson
remained in the batter's box for more than five seconds after the
called strike with his head down, staring at home plate.
</P>
<P>
   Henderson had plenty to say to Welke, however, following his
first ejection of the season -- as did manager Lou Piniella.
</P>
</TEXT>
